    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-03-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="317" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Smith</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-03-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 17,
                            1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 147.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 156, of the 2d
                        instant, reporting that you had informally communicated to the Russian
                        minister of foreign affairs Department’s No. 130, of January 25 last,
                        expressing the sympathy <pb facs="0462" n="374" xml:id="pg_374"/> felt by
                        the United States for the people of Russia. Your action is approved, and I
                        am happy to say that the manifestation of the sympathy of the American
                        people with the famine-stricken sufferers in Russia continues unabated, and
                        but a few days ago a second grain-laden relief ship, the <hi rend="italic">Missouri</hi>, sailed from New York on her errand of mercy.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
